<TITLE> Another BDR man dies at Sylhet hospital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May2 (bdnews24.com)Another BDR member died at Sylhet Osmani Medical College Hospital Saturday. Nayek Renu Mia, 43, of 38 Rifles Battalion hailed from Aambari village of Sunamganj The commander of 38 Rifle Battalion, Col. Gazi Salauddin, told bdnews24.com said, "Renu Mia was admitted to Sylhet Medical College Hospital at 2pm when he felt severe pain in the chest after taking his meal." "He fell unconscious during ECG . The duty doctor declared him dead after he had been shifted to cardiac care unit," Salauddin added. The doctor at the emergency department confirmed the death. Earlier in March, the body of another border guard was recovered from Sylhet BDR headquarters. Nineteen border guards have died so far--four of them committed suicides, seven of heart failure and eight of other diseases. 
